vironment issue, but I should note it.\n\n2. **Designs vs apps drift** - The des
ign files and app files have some differences. The design-spec.md says "实现以 a
pps/phaser3/src/ui/ 为准" which is good.\n\n3. **UIButton.ts issues**:\n   - `se
tTexture` destroys background and recreates it, then calls `setupInteraction()` 
again. This means duplicate event listeners could be attached on the background.
The old listeners aren\'t removed before new ones are added.\n   - Actually look
ing more carefully: `setTexture` destroys `this.background`, then `createBackgro
und()` creates a new one, then `setupInteraction()` is called again. But `setupI
nteraction()` sets interactive on the new background. However, the old Container
-level listeners (like pointerover on target) might still be registered on the o
ld destroyed object? No, because `this.background` reference is replaced and the
old one is destroyed. But `setupInteraction()` adds listeners to `this.backgroun
d`, not to `this`. Wait, it adds to `target` which is `this.background`. So old 
listeners are on the destroyed object. New listeners on new object. That seems o
kay, but there\'s a subtle issue: `this.label` is removed and re-added, but the 
Container\'s `list` might have issues.\n\n4. **UIPanel.ts**:\n   - `createCloseB
utton()` uses `UIIcon` in apps/phaser3 but the design file had inline implementa
tion. The apps version is better.\n   - `destroy()` destroys overlay but if `fro
mScene` is true, the overlay might be double-destroyed? Actually Phaser handles 
this. But the overlay is added directly to scene, not to the Container, so when 
Container is destroyed, overlay isn\'t automatically destroyed. The manual destr
oy is correct.\n\n5. **UIDialog.ts**:\n   - In constructor, `panelConfig` doesn\
't include `onClose` or `onOverlayClick` - it spreads from `config` via `...UIPa
nelConfig`. Wait, `UIDialogConfig extends Omit<UIPanelConfig, \'title\' | \'show
Close\' | \'onClose\' | \'onOverlayClick\'>`. So `onClose` and `onOverlayClick` 
are omitted from the dialog config. But in `panelConfig`, there\'s no `onClose` 
or `onOverlayClick` passed. This means the overlay click in UIPanel constructor 
won\'t have a handler.\n   - Then UIDialog does `if (config.closeOnOverlay && th
is.overlay) { this.overlay.removeAllListeners(\'pointerdown\'); this.overlay.on(
\'pointerdown\', () => this.cancel()); }`\n   - This works, but it\'s modifying 
listeners after construction.\n\n6. **UIToast.ts**:\n   - Line 258: `y: this.y -
10` in `dismiss()`. This is relative to current y, not `baseY`. If `dismiss()` i
s called multiple times, it would drift. PRD-004 5.11 says `y: 0 → -10` (relativ
e to base position). Actually the spec in design-spec.md says `y: 0 → -10` which
means from baseY to baseY - 10. But code uses `this.y - 10` which could be wrong
if called while show animation is in progress.\n   - Actually, looking at `show(
)`: it tweens `y: this.baseY`. And `dismiss()` tweens `y: this.y - 10`. If show(
) is complete, `this.y == this.baseY`, so `this.y - 10 == this.baseY - 10`, whic
h is correct. But if dismiss() is called before show() completes, `this.y` might
be different.\n   - The design-spec says for UIToast dismiss: `y: 0 → -10` which
implies base position to base-10. The code in apps uses `this.y - 10` which is a
relative drift risk.\n   - Similarly for UIAlert `hide()`: it uses `y: this.y - 
10`. Same issue.\n\n7. **UIAlert.ts**:\n   - The design-spec says show() animati
on: `duration=200ms`, `ease=\'Back.out\'`. The code uses `UITweens.popup.duratio
n` (200ms) and `UITweens.popup.ease` (\'Back.out\'). Good.\n   - But the design-
spec for UIAlert hide() says `duration=200ms`, `ease=\'Power2\'`. The code uses 
`UITweens.fade.duration` (150ms) and `UITweens.fade.ease` (\'Power2\'). So the d
uration is 150ms instead of 200ms.\n   - Wait, PRD-004 5.15 says: "退场：alpha: 
1 → 0，y: 0 → -10，duration=200ms，ease=\'Power2\'". The code uses 150ms. This i
s a deviation from PRD-004.\n\n8. **UIButton.ts**:\n   - `setupInteraction()` at
taches events to `this.background`. When `setTexture()` is called, it calls `set
upInteraction()` again, but the old background is destroyed. The new background 
gets new listeners. This is okay.\n   - But there\'s no `destroy()` override to 
clean up listeners. However, since listeners are on `this.background` which is a
child GameObject, when the Container is destroyed, Phaser should clean them up.\
n   - `pointerdown` handler changes fill style but doesn\'t check if it\'s alrea
dy in pressed state.\n\n9. **UISegmentedControl** changes - `id` renamed to `key
`, `selectedId` to `selectedIndex`, `onSelect` to `onChange`. The city-builder w
as updated. But I need to check if there are other callers.\n\n10. **Missing `do
cs/frontend/ui-components.md` update** - The PRD says this should be rewritten, 
but I need to check what was actually changed.\n\n11. **Test coverage**: The tes
ts use `MockScene` and `UIMockScene`. But vitest isn\'t installed so I can\'t ve
rify they pass. Some tests seem superficial - they just check `toBeDefined()` ra
ther than actual behavior.\n\n12. **UIIconButton.ts** - Let me check if it was p
roperly updated.\n\nLet me read a few more files to complete my review.',
    encrypted=None
)
